{"questionId":"9353","questionHtml":"<p>Find the value of <em>θ</em>, giving your answer in radians.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em><strong>METHOD 1</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to use the cosine rule&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>cos <em>θ</em> =&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\frac{{{4^2} + {4^2} - {5^2}}}{{2 \\times 4 \\times 4}}\">\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mn>4</mn>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>+</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mn>4</mn>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n      <mo>−</mo>\n      <mrow>\n        <msup>\n          <mn>5</mn>\n          <mn>2</mn>\n        </msup>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n      <mo>×</mo>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp;(or equivalent) &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>θ</em>&nbsp;= 1.35&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>METHOD 2</strong></em></p>\n<p>attempt to split triangle AOB into two congruent right triangles&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>sin<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\left( {\\frac{\\theta }{2}} \\right) = \\frac{{2.5}}{4}\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mfrac>\n        <mi>θ</mi>\n        <mn>2</mn>\n      </mfrac>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>2.5</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mn>4</mn>\n  </mfrac>\n</math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em>θ</em>&nbsp;= 1.35&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9353","referenceCode":"SPM.2.SL.TZ0.2a","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the value of θ, giving your answer in radians.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"a","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","Topic 3— Geometry and trigonometry","SL 3.4—Circle: radians, arcs, sectors"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}